  "text": "In this section we shall investigate the stability of the cosmological solution (21) , with a Hubble rate as in [CITATION_1] , and explicitly verify our argument that the two scalar fields scalar-tensor theory guarantees the stability of the cosmological solutions. In order to see this, we shall rewrite the FRW equations as a dynamical system, and therefore we introduce the quantities X φ , X χ andȲ , which are defined in terms of the scalar fields φ and χ, in the following way,",
